  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b9a\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc0\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Mustibu nominates Sajith as Prime Minister of an all-party government",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "We expect to nominate Leader of Opposition Sajith Premadasa as the Prime Minister of an all-party government. If his name is nominated for the post of Prime Minister, it is necessary to prove the majority. Therefore, General Secretary of United People's Shakti Ranjith Mathuma Bandara said that he has decided to discuss this with other parties.",
        "He stated this at a press conference held on Sunday (10) at the office of the Leader of the Opposition in Colombo, further mentioning,",
        "For the first time in Sri Lanka's political history, the public has besieged the President's House and Alari House demanding the resignation of the President and Prime Minister.",
        "After this, we asked the President and Prime Minister through the Speaker to step down with the consent of 95 percent of the party leaders in the party leaders' meeting. The President has agreed to this.",
        "President Gotabaya Rajapaksa should step down and form an all-party government not only as a demand of the political party, but also of the Sri Lankan Bar Association, civil society organizations and all religious leaders.",
        "Now is the occasion. We have started discussions with all parties regarding the formation of an all-party government.",
        "At present, according to the Constitution, the Speaker can hold the post of Acting President. After that the person who gets the majority vote in the Parliament can hold the office of President for the rest of the term.",
        "The person elected as the President will hold the office of President till November 17, 2024. Hence it is said that the person who gets the majority support in the Parliament should become the President.",
        "In most countries, in the event of the resignation of the President and the Prime Minister, the name of the opposition leader will be nominated as the new Prime Minister.",
        "Accordingly, we have initiated discussions with other parties regarding the nomination of the Leader of the Opposition as the next Prime Minister.",
        "Accordingly, our position is to appoint the Leader of the Opposition as the Prime Minister with an all-party majority. After that, an all-party government will be formed with the participation of all parties. We have also given an invitation to JVP for this. We expect them to think and act for the future of the country."
      ],
